==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: cut-rate
<hw>cut-rate</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>offering goods or
services at less than standard price or rate; <as>as, <ex>cut-rate</ex>
store</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> cut-price(prenominal).</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>costing less than standard price.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> bargain-priced, cut-price, dirt-cheap.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>cut-rate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: cut-rate
<hw>cut-rate</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a price below the standard
